main event: Two bright objects were observed over Niagara Falls AFB in New York changing from white to orange, moving rapidly and irregularly before disappearing over the horizon.
interesting points: One object was reported to be twice the size of a star and the other three times the size of a star., The sighting lasted between 15 to 30 minutes., The objects were seen under unusually clear atmospheric conditions., The report later identified the objects as Venus and Jupiter., The sighting was corroborated by other GCI sites that reported similar visual observations.
sighted object: two bright objects in the sky
witness description: Military personnel on duty at the air force base
